
npm init
create json file 

installing package local:- 
npm i <package name>

installing package global 
npm i <package name> --g


react more about react app
https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app

1. node_modules Contains all dependencies required by the app. Main dependencies also listed in package.json

2. public Contains static assets including index.html (page template)

index.html
title
fonts
css
favicon
id="root" - our entire app
src In simplest form it's the brain of our app. This is where we will do all of our work. src/index.js is the JavaScript entry point.

3 .gitignore Specifies which files source control (Git) should ignore

4. package.json Every Node.js project has a package.json and it contains info about our project, for example list of dependencies and scripts

5. package-lock.json A snapshot of the entire dependency tree

6. README The markdown file where you can share more info about the project for example build instructions and summary

